<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="366" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1510]" pageId="2" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="366">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named with respect to the religious importance of the 
<typeStatus box="[1135,1183,1376,1402]" pageId="2" pageNumber="366">type</typeStatus>
locality. According to the belief of the local people in Chungthang, the First Sikh Guru visited here in 1509 AD. He blessed this place and spread rice grains as there was no food grown locally. This is the only place in North 
<collectingRegion box="[1104,1185,1447,1473]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="2" pageNumber="366">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
where rice cultivation occurs with his blessings.
</paragraph>
